( logÏƒ) time). This solves our first little problem. The second problem was to exclude suffixes from the output. This can
done by keeping track of the suffix of length  + 1, where  is the current length. To be precise, initially  = 0 and the
ffix of length 1 is the character $, which appears at index idx = 1. Every time  is incremented, we obtain the index of
e suffix of length  + 1 by the assignment idx â† LF (idx). Consequently, a unique substring at index rb is output only if
= idx.
